<SLUG> BC-BBN-DODNOTE-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
VIZCAINO JOINS TEAMMATES ON DISABLED LIST
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MARC J. SPEARS  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM, Calif. _ Scoot over, Bobby Bonilla, Ramon Martinez and
Todd Hollandsworth. Jose Vizcaino needs space on the trainer's
table, too.
</P>
<P>
   A sprained right ankle made Vizcaino the third Dodger since
Friday to be placed on the 15-day disabled list. The shortstop, who
suffered the injury sliding into second base at Colorado on Sunday,
was replaced by Triple-A Albuquerque infielder Wilton Guerrero.
</P>
<P>
   Dodgers trainer Charlie Strasser said Vizcaino, who was on
crutches Monday, is expected to return from the DL on time. Eleven
Dodgers have spent time on the DL this season. Vizcaino's last
appearance on the DL was in 1992 with a torn tendon on his third
left finger.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've had our run-ins with injuries, but it goes in cycles,''
Strasser said.
</P>
<P>
   Guerrero, who started at second base Monday, began the season
with the Dodgers but was sent to Albuquerque on May 16 and demanded
to be traded. With the Dukes, the switch-hitter batted .298 with 36
hits, three doubles and a home run in 121 at-bats.
</P>
<P>
   __ Martinez update: Right-hander Ramon Martinez will receive
season-ending surgery on June 30 to repair his damaged throwing
shoulder. The surgery, which will take place at Inglewood
Centinella Hospital Medical Center, will be on his rotator cuff and
cartilage tears. It will be done by Dodgers team physican Dr. Frank
Jobe and Angels medical director Dr. Lewis Yocum.
</P>
<P>
   The recovery time is expected to be six or seven months for
Martinez, who has a $5.6 million contract next season and a
$600,000 buyout option.
</P>
<P>
   ``Whatever the team decides to do with me next season is fine,''
said Martinez. ``I don't know if I can see myself in another
uniform.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Etc.: Outfielder Todd Hollandsworth, who is out for the
season with a left-shoulder cartilage tear, returned to the team
for the first time since having surgery. His rehabilitation
exercises consist of light-movement exercises... Third baseman
Bobby Bonilla, who was placed on the DL Sunday with an intestinal
infection, returned to Los Angeles Monday morning after a stay in a
Denver hospital. He will be examined by Dodgers physician Dr.
Michael Mellman this morning.... Second baseman Eric Young, who has
missed the last six games with a right-quadriceps strain, is
expected to return to the lineup tonight.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
