schoolteacher issummer vacation. Sounds a little odd, I know, but
it's the truth. Too much free time. Too many decisions to make.
(Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ Over all these years, I've misspelled names
and places, and gotten dates wrong, even matched the wrong person
with an event. And made some bad decisions. But never
intentionally. Neither have any of the people I've worked with. All
this comes to mind because of Patricia Smith, the Boston Globe
columnist and Pulitzer Prize finalist, who was exposed recently as
fabricating quotes, people and events, and forced to resign.
(Kleinberg, Cox News Service) MOVED. EMBARGOED UNTIL 6/24.
