<P>
   TECHTOOLS _ ATLANTA -- I haven't looked at Microsoft Publisher
in several years, and my first glimpse of Publisher 98 was
something of a shock; it appeared to have been dumbed down rather
severely. (Warner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED 6/22.
</P>
<P>
   TECHREPORT _ But times have changed. Now there are cordless
phones for home and wireless phones for the road. Along with those
advances come some potential problems. For instance, you can't be
in two places at once -- at least, not yet -- and if you are on the
road, you're missing calls at home. Oh, sure, you have an answering
machine or voice mail, but to get the messages you'll either have
to go home or remember to dial in. (Kanell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED 6/22.
</P>
<P>
   CYBERSCENE _ ATLANTA -- Long before there were brave surfers
navigating cyberspace, there were men -- and women -- who went to
sea in boats. Whether you are an old hand or just now considering
taking up boating, you can use the sea of information on the World
Wide Web to set a fun and safe course. (Husted, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED 6/22.
</P>
<P>
   JUSTFORFUN _ ALTANTA _ The Velo 500 from Philips is a hand-held
PC whose price and functions land it midway between a personal
digital assistant and a laptop PC. Using Windows CE (the pared-down
version of Windows) as the operating system and 24 megabytes of
memory, the Velo can perform many of the tasks of a portable PC,
including light word processing, connecting to the Internet and
sending and receiving e-mail. (Davis, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
MOVED 6/22.
</P>
<P>
   MACNEWS _ ATLANTA -- If you're looking for a powerful yet
inexpensive alternative to Microsoft's Word 98, check out Nisus
Writer. You can try out Nisus Writer by downloading a free demo
from the company's Web site at
http://www.nisus.com/nisus(underscore)writer.html. Give it try
before automatically opting for Word 98. (Haddad, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED 6/22.
