</P>
<P>
   WARSH-COLUMN (Undated) _ David Warsh's Tuesday column will be
unavailable until after Labor Day.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BKN-DRAFT-GARRITY (Waltham, Mass.) -- It wasn't surprising to
see the 6-foot, 9-inch, 231-pound Pat Garrity among those the
Celtics worked out. Many expect him to be selected in the upper
half of the first round. By Joe Burris. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-OPEN (San Francisco) -- Lee Janzen took home the $535,000
winner's check at the US Open because some golfer had to be
declared the winner, but it was the golf course itself that won. By
Michael Madden.
</P>
<P>
   SOC-WORLDCUP-US (Lyon, France) -- They are among the World Cup
zombies now, wandering around with the Japanese and the Saudis and
the rest of the walking dead. By John Powers.
</P>
<P>
   BOX-SAVARESE (Undated) _ While in preparation for a showdown
with former heavyweight champion Buster Douglas, Lou Savarese
decided that in the long run it was best to go for a short run. By
Ron Borges.
