 UNDATED: ... Pizza Hut.  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   If you are flexible on when and where you want to travel, you
could save a bundle on air fares. A trip to Mexico or the Caribbean
could be just $210 round trip, or a one-way fare to Europe just
$169, all from Boston area airports. The service is through
Airtech, a New York City-based firm that has been finding low fares
for years. For its space-available tickets, Airtech recycles
airlines' unused seats to passengers with flexible schedules.
Tickets can be arranged through the Web at www.airtech.com, by
calling 212-219-7000, or by writing to Airtech, 588 Broadway, Suite
204, New York City, NY 10012.
</P>
<P>
   Young adults 18-22 can travel on AirTran's X-Fares for $35 a
segment. Travel is available to 37 cities and must be completed by
Dec. 15. No travel is allowed on Fridays and Sundays, and only one
small carry-on bag is allowed. For more information and other
restrictions, call 888-493-2737.
</P>
<P>
   Two people traveling together can purchase two first-class round
trip tickets for just $1 more than the price of first-class one-way
tickets on the Thalys high-speed train between Paris and Brussels
and other Belgian cities. Tickets must be purchased between now and
Aug. 30 for travel between July 16 and Aug. 30. For information,
call Rail Europe at 888-382-7245.
</P>
