   &QL; 
 &QL; 
New destination
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Niue, one of the world's largest coral atolls and the smallest
self-governing island in the South Pacific, has opened a US tourist
office to welcome visitors. The island nation has a population of
just 2,200, who depend on tourism as an economic base. The land is
covered with rain forest and dotted with caves and grottoes. The
island is known at The Rock of Polynesia. For information, visit
the Web site at www. &QC; 
nunames.nu, write to SDSI, 1800 112th Ave., NE, Suite 220E,
Bellevue, WA 98004, or call Kathleen Dunlap at 425-688-8513.
</P>
