includes a Concorde flight from New York, three nights'
accommodations, transfers, breakfasts, and a return in business
class to the traveler's city. The package, good July 16-Aug. 31, is
$5,599 a person. Extra nights and a return on the Concorde are
available. For information, call 800-2-FRANCE.
</P>
<P>
   Washington is on a lot of family vacation plans. To make the
visit to the nation's capital memorable, consider the Hay-Adam
``Cool Kids Capital Caper.'' This two-night package includes a two
-oom suite, breakfasts, a dinner, a private car tour, and
accommodations that overlook the White House, the Washington
Monument, or St. John's Church. The hotel, right across the street
from the White House, is a Washington landmark. The weekend package
begins at $1,300 for a family of four. For information, call
800-424-5054.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
Ice skating
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   One way to cool off this summer in New Hampshire is to go ice
skating at the Ice Areana in Waterville Valley. Skating begins July
1 with at least two daily public sessions. Skate rentals are
available. For information, call 603-236-4813.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
Best beaches
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Dr. Beach, a.k.a. Stephen P. Leatherman, has once again named
his top beaches. No New England beach makes the top 10, but one,
Coast Guard Beach on Cape Cod, is No. 18. Leatherman, a professor
at Florida International University of Miami, devises the list
based on 50 criteria within categories that include: physical
factors such as sand softness; wave size and current strength;
biological factors such as water color and quality and presence of
pests; and human-use factors and impacts such as lifeguard
protection, visual obstructions, and amenities.
</P>
<P>
   The top 10 beaches are: Kailua Beach Park, Hawaii; Kaunaoa,
Hawaii; St. Joseph Peninsula State Park, Florida; Wailea, Hawaii;
Caladesi Island State Park, Florida; Hamoa, Hawaii; Cape Florida
SRA, Florida; Hanalei Beach, Hawaii; Fort Desoto Park, Florida; and
St. George Island State Park, Florida.
</P>
<P>
   Leatherman now has a book, ``America's Best Beaches,'' that
discuses a wide variety of beaches along the Atlantic, Gulf, and
Pacific coasts. The $19.95 book can be ordered by calling 888-TOP
BEACHES.
</P>
<P>
   If you're heading for Toronto, check out the student residences
at the University of Toronto at Scarborough. From now to the end of
August, the accommodations are available to all travelers at $80
Canadian ($58 US or less) a night. The townhouses can sleep four to
six people and contain a kitchen. For information, call
416-287-7356.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
