   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ When Money magazine chose the
nation's capital this month as the ``best place to live'' in the
Northeast, eyes rolled. Imagine that a political city with what
President Clinton once called an ``abnormal'' atmosphere could be
considered desirable! But this city has always been better than New
York. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
