took what they learned using Nielsen ratings to track TV viewers
and applied it to the Internet, formed a company, Relevant
Knowledge, and have become a national leaders in tracking Internet
use. (Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   TECH-WOMEN _ Attendance at the major trade show Supercomm
reflected the scarcity of women executives in telecommunications.
At one meeting, 85 people were on the dais, of which three were
women. At Georgia's Advanced Technology Development Center, none of
the executives of 10 start-ups that graduated from the incubator
were women. ``I work with start ups everyday, and I see very few
women,'' says Shawn Grover, an ATDC consultant and president of
Women in Technology, an Atlanta group. (Burritt, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   MONEYTALK _ ATLANTA -- Most experts agree on how to deal with a
stock market as high and as tippy as this one. Don't do anything,
they say.
</P>
<P>
   Their rationale is a sound one: Nobody knows when the market
will decline. Nobody knows how low it will go or how long it will
stay down in the horse latitudes. But everyone knows it will come
back, and eventually the advance will continue. (Ezell, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
