of horse racing, the only person (owner, trainer or jockey) ever to
win five Eclipse Awards. But winning three times in a week isn't a
regular occurrence anymore for Pincay. In 1971, he won 380 times,
more than any rider in the country.
</P>
<P>
   In 1997, he won just 75 races. At 51, Pincay is fighting the
record book and the calendar simultaneously. He wants to become the
all-time winningest jockey, but he is running out of time.
(Crittenden, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
