<SLUG> BC-LETTERMAN-WEBSITE-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LETTERMAN SNARED ON WEB SITE WRITTEN BY HIS STAFFERS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOMMY CUMMINGS 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   From the home office in ...
</P>
<P>
   It's the Official Late Show With David Letterman Web site
(www.cbs.com), created by Worldwide Pants and CBS News Media, and
packed with late-night comedy.
</P>
<P>
   In a news release announcing the launch of his site, Letterman
had only one comment: ``This really means a lot to me, because I
met my lovely wife, Kathie Lee, on the Internet.''
</P>
<P>
   Letterman has always had a following on the Internet, but CBS'
site is the first official production written by Letterman staffers
and not some network weasels.
</P>
<P>
   A few highlights:
</P>
<P>
   The Top Ten Extra: Jokes that didn't make it into Letterman's
top-10 list.
</P>
<P>
   Dave's Comedy Review: Audio with Letterman and cue-card boy Tony
Mendez.
</P>
<P>
   Dave TV: More audio, with comedy bits and guest interviews.
</P>
<P>
   Late Show Comedy: Dave's Record Collection, fan e-mail, CBS
Bookmobile.
</P>
<P>
   Dave's Online Clubhouse: A potpourri of games, puzzles and daily
quizzes hosted by some of ``The Late Show's'' more familiar faces:
Calvert DeForest, Biff Henderson, Mujibur and Sirajul, and deli
owner Rupert Jee.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Here's an odd trend:
</P>
<P>
   A survey by the Pew Research Center (www.people-press.org) found
that an estimated 36 million people get some news from the Internet
in a typical week, compared with 11 million who did so two years
ago.
</P>
<P>
   A Business Week/Harris Executive Poll says only 24 percent of
executives surveyed use the Internet to sell products or services
directly to customers. Most of those who do not sell over the
Internet say they have no plans to do so, the survey found.
</P>
<P>
   (Tommy Cummings reviews Web sites for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. E-mail him at: dragon(at)star-telegram.com. Visit
the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
