 &HT;    THE GEORGE CLOONEY FILE
 &HT;    By Phil Kloer
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   -- Born: May 6, 1961, Lexington, Ky.
</P>
<P>
   -- Family: Father is Nick Clooney, former Los Angeles TV
anchorman and now American Movie Classics host; aunt is singer
Rosemary Clooney; uncle was the late actor Jose Ferrer; cousin is
actor Miguel Ferrer.
</P>
<P>
   -- Personal: Divorced; lives with Celine Balitian, 24, a law
student he met in France. Both Balitian and Julianna Marguiles (who
plays Clooney's ``ER'' love) were both listed in People magazine's
1998 Most Beautiful People issue, and Clooney was the magazine's
Sexiest Man Alive in 1997.
</P>
<P>
   -- Hobbies: Basketball, golf, collecting motorcycles.
</P>
<P>
   -- Early career: Several TV failures (``Baby Talk,'' ``Sunset
Beat'' and semi-successes (a cop on ``Sisters,'' a neighbor on
``The Facts of Life'').
</P>
<P>
   -- Big break: Cast as Dr. Doug Ross on ``ER'' in 1994.
</P>
<P>
   -- Movies: ``From Dusk Till Dawn,'' ``One Fine Day,'' ``The
Peacemaker,'' ``Batman &AMP; Robin,'' ``Out of Sight'' (opens Friday).
</P>
<P>
   -- What's next: A small role in Terrence Malick's ``The Thin Red
Line''; feature film ``Leatherheads,'' about the early days of
football; a development deal with CBS in which he'll produce series
and possibly live dramas.
</P>
