<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Wednesday, June 24 and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact James Laurin at the Daily News,
(818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   ROSY-ECON-OUTLOOK (Los Angeles) _ California's economy, robust
enough to shrug off a withering financial calamity in Asia, should
continue on a strong growth curve through 2000, according to a
widely watched survey. Job gains over the next two years will
likely rival the strong spurts of the 1970s and 1980s, said the
quarterly UCLA Anderson Forecast. By Gregory J. Wilcox.
</P>
<P>
   DISNEY-ABC-MOVES (Los Angeles) _ The Walt Disney Co. plans to
move up to 400 ABC employees from its New York headquarters to a
new building on the Disney lot in suburban Burbank by the middle of
2000. In addition, ABC entertainment offices in nearby Century City
will move to Burbank, giving the butt of Johnny Carson jokes
another boost of civic pride. By Dave McNary.
</P>
