<P>
   CoxNet will move the following stories from the Lufkin Daily
News this evening.
</P>
<P>
   COX-JASPER-KLAN _ JASPER, Texas _ Lawmen and representatives
from the state attorney general's office say they have not
developed any loopholes that would prevent members of the Ku Klux
Klan from conducting their scheduled Saturday rally in Jasper.
</P>
<P>
   COX-JASPER-RESPONSE _ JASPER, Texas _ Civic leaders here
politely issued a similar statement Tuesday both to the media and
to supremacist organizations: Leave us alone.
</P>
<P>
   ``What would help us a lot is for all of y'all to go home, for
all of these radical groups to go home,'' Jasper County Sheriff
Billy Rowles told a group of about 20 reporters and television
cameramen in front of the county courthouse. ``Let Jasper's
citizens, the good people in our county, deal with what has taken
place.
</P>
