High School Scholastic Chess Championship in Phoenix. Next month
the All-Star Knights travel to Moscow for the World Youth Games.
(Librado Romero/New York Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) UNDATED -- June 23, 1998 -- FISH-LOGO, 6-23 -- For eight
years this logo depicting the state, an outstretched hand, a family
of four in silhouette and a fish has been used by the town of
Republic, Mo. Recently, controversy has surrounded the logo's fish.
``The fish symbol, also known as an ichthus, first appeared in the
second century and was used as a secret sign of Christianity,''
says volunteer ACLU lawyer Doug Bonney in a letter to the town.
Debates like this one in Republic over the separation of church and
state are coming up with increasing regularity around the country.
(New York Times Photo)
</P>
