<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, JUNE 24
</HEADLINE>
  Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-SUMMIT-CLINTON-NYT (moved on Friday, June 19)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, June 19,
about President Clinton's preparations for his trip to China
included an incorrect interpretation of remarks by Robert A. Kapp,
president of the United States-China Business Council. While Mr.
Kapp said foreign visitors to China should be sensitive to their
hosts, he did not link the observation to President Bush's 1989
visit to Beijing, in which the White House invited a prominent
dissident to a banquet.
</P>
<P>
   BC-VIAGRA-INSURANCE-NYT (moved on Friday, June 19)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, June 19,
about insurance coverage for Viagra misstated Medicaid policy on
paying for it. Federal officials have said they expect to require
Medicaid payments for Viagra, not deny them, when a doctor says the
drug is medically necessary.
</P>
<P>
   BC-MERRILL-MIDLAND-NYT (moved on Monday, June 22)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, June 22,
about an agreement by Merrill Lynch &AMP; Company to buy Midland Walwyn
for $855 million misstated what the purchase price represents. It
is 21 times Midland's earnings for its last fiscal year, not 21
times the firm's book value.
</P>
</TEXT>
